cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 250 miles WSW of Grand Cayman
cyclone.trajectory: Forecast to move ENE toward Cuba, turn N-NW across the Florida Keys/South Florida late Sunday-Monday, then curve back N-NE across the peninsula and exit the Atlantic near northeast Florida by Wednesday.
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Keys or extreme South Florida

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical Storm Watch from Sebastian Inlet southward around the Florida peninsula to Bonita Beach, including Lake Okeechobee, the Florida Keys, and Florida Bay.
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning for the Cayman Islands, portions of central Cuba, and the north-western Bahamas.
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Entire Florida peninsula (Keys through northeast coast), Cuba, NW Bahamas, eastern Gulf coast.
weather_observation.wind: Only a very small (≤3%) chance of sustained tropical-storm-force winds; breezy conditions with occasional gusts possible Wednesday.
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minor coastal water rise <2 ft possible around Wednesday during onshore flow.
weather_observation.rainfall: Bands of rain mid-week could bring 1–3 inches; widespread 4-inch totals are not expected at Jacksonville.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Rough seas and dangerous rip currents for coastal and offshore operations beginning mid-week.
